description.narrative:
The main objective is to reduce poverty especially among young rural women who are the most economically and socially vulnerable, and to promote empowerment and gender equality among these young women. 

The project goal is to improve the lives and livelihoods of 5250 young rural women in Chikhwawa District by providing them with a three-year skills development in modern farming, nutrition, sanitation and environmental improvement practices so they can increase their food production, improve household food security, nutrition and increase household income.;The main objective is to reduce poverty especially among young rural women who are the most economically and socially vulnerable, and to promote empowerment and gender equality among these young women. 

The project goal is to improve the lives and livelihoods of 5250 young rural women in Chikhwawa District by providing them with a three-year skills development in modern farming, nutrition, sanitation and environmental improvement practices so they can increase their food production, improve household food security, nutrition and increase household income.;
